eason": null, "body": "I guess we could do it manually but quick search brought me to  https://argcomplete.readthedocs.org which seems to be quite neat:\nfollowing minimal intrusion:\n\n```\n$> git diff\ndiff --git a/datalad/cmdline/main.py b/datalad/cmdline/main.py\nindex 5c4c88a..5e5de9a 100644\n--- a/datalad/cmdline/main.py\n+++ b/datalad/cmdline/main.py\n@@ -10,7 +10,7 @@\n\n __docformat__ = 'restructuredtext'\n\n-\n+import argcomplete\n import argparse\n import logging\n import sys\n@@ -172,6 +172,7 @@ def generate_api_call(cmdlineargs=None):\n\n def main(cmdlineargs=None):\n     parser = setup_parser()\n+    argcomplete.autocomplete(parser)\n     # parse cmd args\n     cmdlineargs = parser.parse_args(cmdlineargs)\n     # run the function associated with the selected command\n```\n\npros: allows to define extended completions (e.g. handles, collections) within python code itself.  Should generally be more homogeneous with the rest\n\ncons: additional 3rd party dependence (present in Debian/ubuntus), requires its own installation within completions system\n", "closed_by": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https